<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,375,1527,1551]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="539">Paspalum pilosum</emphasis>
Lam.
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[167,778,1567,1764]" pageId="32" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,330,1567,1591]" pageId="32" pageNumber="539">Identification.</emphasis>
Perennial, tussock, or decumbent grass, 
<quantity box="[168,275,1601,1625]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" metricValueMax="9.5" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="539" unit="cm" value="62.5" valueMax="95.0" valueMin="30.0">30–95 cm</quantity>
height. Leaf-blades plane, lanceolate, 
<quantity box="[685,778,1602,1626]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="0.3" pageId="32" pageNumber="539" unit="cm" value="15.0" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="3.0">3–27 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[228,348,1636,1660]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="539" unit="cm" value="0.55" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.7 cm</quantity>
wide, covered with hairs on both sides, ligulate. It is diagnosed by its inflorescence with one sin- gle branch, 7.5–16.0 cm long, with small trichomes and paired spikelets.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="539" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[168,780,1780,1838]" pageId="32" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,279,1780,1804]" pageId="32" pageNumber="539">Remarks.</emphasis>
Observed more frequently on disturbed sites like roadsides, but also occurring on the native grassland.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[166,778,1854,1947]" pageId="32" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,354,1854,1878]" pageId="32" pageNumber="539">Brazilian range.</emphasis>
Midwest (except MS state), North (AM, PA and RO states), Northeast (BA, MA and PE states), South (
<collectingRegion box="[245,335,1923,1947]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="32" pageNumber="539">PR state</collectingRegion>
) and Southeast (except ES state) regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
